# Low-poly carabiner-like frame (approximation) for visualization.
# Units: meters. Coordinate frame: X right, Y out of plane, Z up.
# This mesh is an assembly of several boxes to approximate the D-shape frame.

o frame

# Box helper convention used here:
# Each box is defined by 8 vertices and 12 triangular faces.
# Vertex order for a box centered at (cx,cy,cz) with half-sizes (hx,hy,hz):
# 1 (-x,-y,-z), 2 (+x,-y,-z), 3 (+x,+y,-z), 4 (-x,+y,-z)
# 5 (-x,-y,+z), 6 (+x,-y,+z), 7 (+x,+y,+z), 8 (-x,+y,+z)

# -------------------------
# Box A: left vertical bar
# center (-0.030, 0, 0.045), size (0.012, 0.010, 0.090)
